io.github.prolobjectlink.prolog

Interface PrologMapping<O>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - Java Object implicit in the conversion.

    public interface PrologMapping<O>
    PrologMapping is an interface for custom converters. The users classes implementing this interface for configure a special conversion from PrologTerm to Java Object and to Java Object to PrologTerm. When registered into a conversion context, a converter adds to the defined conversions a new mapping.
    Since:
    1.1
    Author:
    Jose Zalacain
